verses.text:
Let me go where'er the going, To the mansions of the blest;
Let me join the people's rest; I would gain the realms of light,
Let me go, 'tis Jesus calls me, Let me go to the rest of day; I want to be away.

Let me go where none are weary,
Where is raised no note of woe;
Let me go and back not tarry;
Let the rough angels know;
Let me go where Jesus beckons,
Lures my soul away, away,
And the Victor's song triumphant
Thrills my heart, I cannot stay.
